Enums.name: DocumentType
Enums.description: The type of the patient document, such as 'note' (text document) or 'fhirBundle' (FHIR JSON document).

Enums.name: ClinicalDocumentType
Enums.description: The type of the clinical document.

Enums.name: DocumentContentSourceType
Enums.description:
The type of the content's source. 
In case the source type is 'inline', the content is given as a string (for instance, text). 
In case the source type is 'reference', the content is given as a URI.

Enums.description: The type of the Onco Phenotype inference.

Enums.name: JobStatus
Enums.description: The status of the processing job.

values.name: accepted
values.description: If the request was accepted and the server guarantees that the server state reflects a single execution of the operation.

values.name: rejected
values.description:
If the request was rejected because the combination of Repeatability-First-Sent and Repeatability-Request-ID were invalid
or because the Repeatability-First-Sent value was outside the range of values held by the server.

Models.name: OncoPhenotypeData
Models.description: The body of the Onco Phenotype request.

properties.name: patients
properties.description: The list of patients, including their clinical information and data.

valueType.name: PatientRecord
valueType.description: A patient record, including their clinical information and data.

properties.name: id
properties.description: A given identifier for the patient. Has to be unique across all patients in a single request.

properties.name: info
properties.description: Patient structured information, including demographics and known structured clinical information.

type.name: PatientInfo
type.description: Patient structured information, including demographics and known structured clinical information.

properties.name: sex
properties.description: The patient's sex.

properties.name: birthDate
properties.description: The patient's date of birth.

properties.name: clinicalInfo
properties.description: Known clinical information for the patient, structured.

valueType.name: ClinicalCodedElement
valueType.description: A piece of clinical information, expressed as a code in a clinical coding system.

properties.name: system
properties.description: The clinical coding system, e.g. ICD-10, SNOMED-CT, UMLS.

properties.name: code
properties.description: The code within the given clinical coding system.

properties.name: name
properties.description: The name of this coded concept in the coding system.

properties.name: value
properties.description: A value associated with the code within the given clinical coding system.

properties.name: data
properties.description: Patient unstructured clinical data, given as documents.

valueType.name: PatientDocument
valueType.description: A clinical document related to a patient. Document here is in the wide sense - not just a text document (note).

properties.name: type
properties.description: The type of the patient document, such as 'note' (text document) or 'fhirBundle' (FHIR JSON document).

properties.name: clinicalType
properties.description: The type of the clinical document.

properties.name: id
properties.description: A given identifier for the document. Has to be unique across all documents for a single patient.

properties.name: language
properties.description: A 2 letter ISO 639-1 representation of the language of the document.

properties.name: createdDateTime
properties.description: The date and time when the document was created.

properties.name: content
properties.description: The content of the patient document.

type.name: DocumentContent
type.description: The content of the patient document.

properties.name: sourceType
properties.description:
The type of the content's source.
In case the source type is 'inline', the content is given as a string (for instance, text).
In case the source type is 'reference', the content is given as a URI.

properties.name: value
properties.description: The content of the document, given either inline (as a string) or as a reference (URI).

properties.name: configuration
properties.description: Configuration affecting the Onco Phenotype model's inference.

type.name: OncoPhenotypeModelConfiguration
type.description: Configuration affecting the Onco Phenotype model's inference.

properties.name: verbose
properties.description: An indication whether the model should produce verbose output.

properties.name: includeEvidence
properties.description: An indication whether the model's output should include evidence for the inferences.

properties.name: inferenceTypes
properties.description:
A list of inference types to be inferred for the current request.
This could be used if only part of the Onco Phenotype inferences are required.
If this list is omitted or empty, the model will return all the inference types.

properties.name: checkForCancerCase
properties.description: An indication whether to perform a preliminary step on the patient's documents to determine whether they relate to a Cancer case.

properties.name: jobId
properties.description: A processing job identifier.

properties.description: The date and time when the processing job was created.

properties.description: The date and time when the processing job is set to expire.

properties.name: lastUpdateDateTime
properties.description: The date and time when the processing job was last updated.

properties.name: code

properties.name: code
properties.description: One of a server-defined set of error codes.

properties.name: innererror

properties.name: inferences
properties.description: The model's inferences for the given patient.

valueType.name: OncoPhenotypeInference
valueType.description: An inference made by the Onco Phenotype model regarding a patient.

properties.name: type
properties.description: The type of the Onco Phenotype inference

properties.name: value
properties.description: The value of the inference, as relevant for the given inference type.

properties.name: description
properties.description: The description corresponding to the inference value.

properties.name: confidenceScore
properties.description: Confidence score for this inference.

properties.name: evidence
properties.description: The evidence corresponding to the inference value.

valueType.name: InferenceEvidence
valueType.description: A piece of evidence corresponding to an inference.

properties.name: patientDataEvidence
properties.description: A piece of evidence from a clinical note (text document).

type.name: ClinicalNoteEvidence
type.description: A piece of evidence from a clinical note (text document).

properties.name: id
properties.description: The identifier of the document containing the evidence.

properties.name: text
properties.description: The actual text span which is evidence for the inference.

properties.name: offset
properties.description: The start index of the evidence text span in the document (0 based).

properties.name: length
properties.description: The length of the evidence text span.

properties.name: patientInfoEvidence
properties.description:
A piece of clinical information, expressed as a code in a clinical coding
system.

properties.name: importance
properties.description: A value indicating how important this piece of evidence is for the inference.

properties.name: caseId
properties.description: An identifier for a clinical case, if there are multiple clinical cases regarding the same patient.

properties.name: modelVersion
properties.description: The version of the model used for inference, expressed as the model date.
